data.chText: （用油性或稀软物质）胡乱涂抹
data.enText: to spread an oily or soft substance over a surface in a rough or careless way

data.chText: 那几个孩子往墙上抹了泥巴。
data.enText: The children had smeared mud on the walls.

data.chText: 那几个孩子往墙上抹了泥巴。
data.enText: The children had smeared the walls with mud.
to make sth dirty or greasy
His glasses were smeared.
smeared windows
to damage sb's reputation by saying unpleasant things about them that are not true

data.chText: 这篇报道企图玷污该党领袖的声誉。
data.enText: The story was an attempt to smear the party leader.

data.chText: 把（字迹、图画等）蹭得模糊不清；变得模糊不清
data.enText: to rub writing, a drawing, etc. so that it is no longer clear; to become not clear in this way

data.chText: 信的最后几个字蹭得看不清了。
data.enText: The last few words of the letter were smeared.
an oily or dirty mark
a smear of jam
a story that is not true about sb that is intended to damage their reputation, especially in politics

data.chText: 他受到对方的毁谤攻击。
data.enText: He was a victim of a smear campaign .

data.text: mark ♦ stain ♦ streak ♦ speck ♦ blot ♦ smear ♦ spot

data.chText: 以上各词均指污点、斑点、污迹。
data.enText: These are all words for a small area of dirt or another substance on a surface.
mark
a small area of dirt or other substance on the surface of sth, especially one that spoils its appearance

data.chText: 孩子们把厨房的地板弄得污迹斑斑。
data.enText: The kids left dirty marks all over the kitchen floor.
stain
a dirty mark on sth that is difficult to remove, especially one made by a liquid
blood stains
streak
a long thin mark or line that is a different colour from the surface it is on
She had streaks of grey in her hair.
speck
a very small mark, spot or piece of a substance on sth
There isn't a speck of dust anywhere in the house.
blot
a spot or dirty mark left on sth by a substance such as ink or paint being dropped on a surface
smear
a mark made by sth such as oil or paint being spread or rubbed on a surface
spot
a small dirty mark on sth
There were grease spots all over the walls.
a streak/speck/blot/smear/spot of sth
a dirty mark/stain/streak/speck/smear/spot
an ink mark/stain/blot/spot
a(n) oil/grease/paint mark/stain/spot
to leave a mark/stain/streak/speck/blot/smear/spot
to get a mark/stain/spot out of sth

means: (用油性或稀软物质)胡乱涂抹
把（字迹、图画等）蹭得模糊不清

tr: an act that brings discredit to the person who does it
example: he made a huge blot on his copybook
he had a smudge on his cheek

tr: a thin tissue or blood sample spread on a glass slide and stained for cytologic examination and diagnosis under a microscope
charge falsely or with malicious intent
attack the good name and reputation of someone
example: The journalists have defamed me!" "The article in the paper sullied my reputation

tr: cover (a surface) by smearing (a substance) over it
stain by smearing or daubing with a dirty substance

value.def: If you smear a surface with an oily or sticky substance or smear the substance onto the surface, you spread a layer of the substance over the surface.

example.ex: My sister smeared herself with suntan oil and slept by the swimming pool...
example.tran: 我姐姐在身上抹了防晒油，躺在游泳池边睡着了。

example.ex: Smear a little olive oil over the inside of the salad bowl.
example.tran: 在色拉碗的内壁上抹一点橄榄油。

value.def: A smear is a dirty or oily mark.

example.ex: There was a smear of gravy on his chin.

value.def: To smear someone means to spread unpleasant and untrue rumours or accusations about them in order to damage their reputation.

example.ex: ...an attempt to smear the director-general of the BBC.
example.tran: 污蔑英国广播公司主管的企图

value.def: A smear is an unpleasant and untrue rumour or accusation that is intended to damage someone's reputation.

example.ex: He puts all the accusations down to a smear campaign by his political opponents.
example.tran: 他把所有的指责都归结为政治对手们的造谣攻势。

value.def: A smear or a smear test is a medical test in which a few cells are taken from a woman's cervix and examined to see if any cancer cells are present.
value.tran: 涂片检查(对妇女子宫颈取样检查癌变的一种方法)

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 pap smear, pap test

trans: 涂片试验(从妇女子宫颈取少许组织，以检查是否有癌细胞)
